      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK AMETHYST (3) jumps from box 3 for the first time after scoring at Angle Park (19.69) in a Grade 5. Has never been out of the money in eight starts this distance. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. CULBURRA (7) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (16.96) last time out at this track. Has never been out of the money in eight starts this course. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. ZINFANDEL TRACE (5) last appeared when too good (29.70) over 512m at Mt Gambier on March 29. Resumes after finishing sixth (29.70) at Mt Gambier over 512m three-and-a-half months ago. Looks well placed here and has the ability. Go well. KING TOBY (1) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to bounce back.",
